Subject: You are invited to bid Body: February 18,2008
To:
Request for Proposal for 2008 National Association of Student Financial Aid Aadministrators (NASFAA) conference booth design and logistics
Dear ,
You are invited to submit a proposal for our 2008 NASFAA conference booth design and logistic in accordance with the requirements set forth in the attached request for proposal (RFP).
Company profile: American Student Assistance is a private, federally funded, nonprofit organization whose mission is to help students and parents manage higher education debt. Incorporated in 1956, ASA was the nation's first private student loan guarantee agency and a model for the federal student loan guarantee program. As an administrator of the Federal Family Education Loan Program, ASA delivers quality default prevention, guarantee, origination and fund delivery services to students, parents, schools and lenders nationwide. ASA guarantees more than $2 billion in student loans annually and currently manages a student loan portfolio worth more than $20 billion. Based in Boston, American Student Assistance employs more than 600 associates nationwide. Visit www.amsa.com for more information.
RFPs are due by Wednesday February 27, 2008. They will be reviewed and all vendors will be notified whether they are disqualified, rejected or chosen as a finalist by Friday February 29, 2008. All finalists will be contacted for phone interviews the week of March 3 , 2008. A decision will be made by Monday March 10, 2008.
I will be the single point of contact for all inquiries and correspondences.
I thank you for your time, effort, and interest in our 2008 NASFAA conference presence Sincerely,
Nancy Meehan Events Manager American Student Assistance 100 Cambridge Street, Suite 1600 Boston, Ma 02114 1-800-999-9080 Ext. 4207 Fax 617-521-6154 nmeehan@amsa.com
Attachment: 2008 NASFAA RFP
